{"submission_id":"sub_6223ebe1a4c731c0","run_id":"2026-06-23T16-29-38-293Z_1400822-23768cec_ingest_meeting-doc-201671","submitted_at":"2026-06-23T16:37:53.182Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:6223ebe1a4c731c0b22934675d943d2e9a631b1cee8f313c77c7488aff703356","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_201671","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_fuel_hedge_program_description","label":"Fuel Hedging Program Description","raw_text":"MTA's fuel hedging program mitigates budget risk by dollar cost averaging approximately 50% of projected fuel expenses. The goal of the program is to be 50% hedged for the next 12 months. Monthly hedges are equal to approximately 4% of the projected fuel purchases expected to occur 13-24 months from each hedge execution date. The actual percentage hedged could be higher or lower than the 50% target depending on the actual levels of fuel consumption. While the fuel heding program includes compressed natrual gas, there are currently no actve hedges.","payload":{"claim_text":"MTA's fuel hedging program mitigates budget risk by dollar cost averaging approximately 50% of projected fuel expenses. The goal of the program is to be 50% hedged for the next 12 months. Monthly hedges are equal to approximately 4% of the projected fuel purchases expected to occur 13-24 months from each hedge execution date. The actual percentage hedged could be higher or lower than the 50% target depending on the actual levels of fuel consumption."},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_201671","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_201671#p001_b0033","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_201671/blocks.jsonl","page_number":1,"block_id":"p001_b0033","text_sha256":"sha256:f9f8a173491325bc61eed9bcff5d0fe8101aeed749a041302f323222ab2db6e4","text_source":"raw_text","role":"program_note"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
